==English==
===Etymology===
*from Balaklava in the Crimea type of [[skimask]] used by British troops in bitter cold weather.

===Noun===
'''balaclava'''
#A warm [[cap]] shielding the [[neck]] and [[head]], often made out of [[wool]].

